Package nl.naturalis.geneious.name

Classes and interfaces shared by the AB1/Fasta Import operation and the Split Name operation.
Author:
Ayco Holleman
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Annotator
    Responsible for creating annotations, versioning documents, copying annotations from dummy documents to real documents, and for deleting obsolete dummy documents.
    DefaultSequenceInfo
    A subclass of {link SequenceInfo} exclusively used by the Split Name operation.
    NameUtil
    Utility methods shared by the AB1/Fasta Import operation and the Split Name operation.
    QueryCache
    Provides various types of lookups on a collection of Geneious documents, presumably fetched-and-cached using a database query.
    QueryCache.Key
    A compound key that is likely to be useful as a key for the query cache.
    SequenceInfo
    SequenceInfo objects are responsible for producing the annotations for a document.
    SequenceNameParser
    Parses an AB1 file name or fasta sequence header and creates a NaturalisNote from the extracted information.
    StorableDocument
    A wrapper around the Geneious-native AnnotatedPluginDocument class along with a SequenceInfo object that will provide the annotations for the document.
    VersionTracker
    Keeps track of, and hands out version numbers for documents based on their DocumentType and name (not including name suffixes like ".ab1", " (ab1)" and " (fasta)").
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    NotParsableException
    Thrown when the name of an AB1 file or the header of a fasta sequence could not be broken up into meaningful segments.
